    The V0/V1 era covered here: Vue 3 source compiles to standards-based
    custom elements via <code>defineCustomElement</code>, ships to Vue,
    Angular, AEM, and any HTML, and gets backed by a custom
    <code>axs-automation</code> Nx plugin that handles scaffolding, IDE
    metadata, docs, and recipes. Three case studies on this site cover
