  <h2 class="section-title">the seven libraries</h2>
  <p>
    Everything lives in one Nx monorepo. Seven libraries, each independently
    versioned and published:
  </p>

  <dl class="stack-list">
    <dt>axs-vue</dt>
    <dd>
      <strong>~104 Vue 3 components</strong>, the canonical source.
      Forms, charts, modals, navigation, layouts, the lot. Built as Vue
      single-file components so designers and engineers share one mental
      model.
    </dd>
    <dt>axs-web-components</dt>
    <dd>
      <strong>~54 custom elements</strong>, the standards-based output.
      Each one wraps a Vue SFC via <code>defineCustomElement</code> and
      registers it with the global registry. Framework-agnostic consumers
      use these directly.
    </dd>
    <dt>axs-angular</dt>
    <dd>
      Angular-flavored adapters and typed wrappers over the same custom
      elements. Angular apps get typed templates without diverging from
      the source of truth.
    </dd>
    <dt>axs-core</dt>
    <dd>
      Shared composables, directives, types, styles, and the foundation
      utilities every component builds on.
    </dd>
    <dt>axs-styles</dt>
    <dd>
      Design tokens as CSS custom properties. Spacing, typography, color,
      breakpoints, everything that pierces shadow DOM via the
      cascade.
    </dd>
    <dt>axs-vue-recipes</dt>
    <dd>
      Pre-composed multi-component patterns, the &ldquo;here&rsquo;s
      how to build a labeled-input-with-validation&rdquo; layer.
      Discoverable via Storybook and the MCP server (see
      <a href="/case-studies/07-axs-ai-architecture">AXS + AI deep dive</a>).
    </dd>
    <dt>axs-automation</dt>
    <dd>
      The custom Nx plugin we built ourselves. Generators
      (<code>create-component</code>, <code>vue-recipe</code>,
      <code>angular-recipe</code>) and executors (<code>doc-gen</code>,
      <code>jweb-types</code>, <code>vcustom-html</code>,
      <code>build-icon-blueprint</code>) that automate everything around
      component lifecycle.
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <h2 class="section-title">vue source → custom elements</h2>
  <p>
    The architectural premise. One Vue 3 single-file component, exposed as
    a standards-based custom element. Any Vue app, Angular app, AEM
    template, or plain HTML page renders the same tag and gets the same
    behavior, same styles, same events, same accessibility tree.
  </p>

  <Code code={defineComponentsSample} lang="typescript" theme={theme} />

