    <code>libs/axs-web-components/src/defineComponents.ts</code> &middot;
    Vue 3 + <code>defineCustomElement</code>
  </p>

  <p>
    This is the direct successor to the FASET <code>vue-custom-element</code>
    pattern, now built into Vue 3 itself. Same architecture, no third-party
    runtime adapter, full TypeScript types.
  </p>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <h2 class="section-title">build-time IDE metadata (axs-automation:jweb-types)</h2>
  <p>
    The IDE-awareness foundation. At every build, an Nx executor walks
    every Vue SFC, runs it through <code>vue-docgen-api</code>, extracts
    props (with type info), events, slots, and emits two files:
    <code>axs.web-types.json</code> (JetBrains schema) and
    <code>axs.html-data.json</code> (VS Code custom HTML data). Both
    declared in <code>package.json</code> so any editor that installs
    the package gets autocomplete automatically.
  </p>

  <Code code={jwebTypesSample} lang="typescript" theme={theme} />

